caption: I've been wanting to try Lolo's for a while and was a little skeptical... boy was I missing out. Easily one of the best crablegs and shrimp I've ever had. We ordered the crableg steampot with the garlic and old bay and it was a hit. Will certainly be back and try other things on the menu soon.
Food was great service was good. Definitely would go back
(Translated by Google) Good food Good food  (Original) Good food Buena comida
So delicious. The softshell crab sandwich was divine. The garlic fries were delicious 🤤🤤.
Great food
The food was seasoned well and we loved the ambiance in the "shack".  Tip: make a reservation.
Food arrived warm but the garlic crema wings and jerk ribs so good and delivery person provided excellent cautious service.
Loved this place! Best crab legs I’ve ever had! I’ll be back soon !!! Awesome food and service.
I like to go there because they very friendly and I love the food

This place is truly amazing great food fresh hot good portion worth every penny if fresh seafood is your thing this is the place to go and tell em Chef Sylvia sent you this place is a true experience every one should have
The food, atmosphere and service was fantastic!  Scallops with crab risotto was wonderful- creamy and so much crab.  Others had whole crab which they loved.  Would recommend to any and all!
Really great clam chowder (topped with crab !!), garlic roasted crab, and LoLo's Seafood Shack penne. All of the seasonings were on point. The tiramisu was delicious as well.
This place was amazing. Great food. Great view and service was great also. Very good bar menu and food.

Rustic shack in the backyard - stairs going to the backyard. Picnic benches in the shack. Offers front curbside eating as well. Happy hour  4-6pm, the slushy is really good. Had coconut rum with mine. Attentive service. It's a hole in the wall that serve good food!!
The clam chowder in the bread bowl is to die for and the lobster was amazing! The views are nice and the service was very friendly and we didn't have to wait for a table

The eating space is in the back and you better bring a coat and some gloves because ventilation is serious. The heater doesn't work well enough to cover the entirety of the space. So your best bet is to sit in front of it. The food was average at best. Flavor was mediocre. Best thing to do for bang for your buck is to go for combos as buying the food individually is  for the flavor. too much butter sometimes whole block drenched in sauce. The sides aren't spectacular either. Less than average but better than subpar. The dirty rice isnt dirty, its just bland. You can make any side better at home. Consider the time of day when going as you may catch them when they're at their worst. This was done in the night after 8p.  Plus side, the wait staff that worked were VERY friendly and accommodating considering the circumstances. Best part of the restaurant. Just wish the food quality matched 😓

So so good! I had the fish tacos, an easy first order. My expectations were very low; city fish tacos are typically pretty meh but these did not disappoint! The flavor was everything: just a lotta whole lotta! My only recommendation would be to eat it there vs traveling. It wasn’t trash to travel with but it would’ve been perfect if I hadn’t.
An oasis

Came inside for a Valentine's Dinner for 2 and we were given royal treatment start to end BUT the food fell very flat in flavor and and the variety of flavors were also quiet. Our Server Mike was very attentive and professional and he and the frontman and other lady were very professional and humourous. They brought us a free glass of champagne. Despite all of this, I have to point out that the backyard enclosure is still too cold, the servers brought out our sides before the seafood boils were done which led to our sides being cold as soon as our boils were served...not cool. The corn and wok charred cauliflower was undercooked and hard but my partner's broccoli was well cooked, yet flat in flavor. The ginger butter boil was flat. The rice and beans was also flat. I would go back when the food improves

One of my fav places in Harlem. Lately, the quality of my orders have not been up to par. Pom Pom shrimp Is my favorite and it seems like it’s a hit or miss lately. My shrimp is dry with just sauce topped on it, no batter. No longer a favorite.

The service was good and the food was decent as well. The best part about the restaurant is probably the views! We had an inside table so unfortunately we missed out on that - but would go back again!

Food was bland and a small amount I ordered online spent 105 bucks and they got my order wrong put curry on my food and I ask for something else !! To much money and no flavor on anything I ordered sorry no more business from me
This place has some good food i recommend this place to everyone
I ordered the spicy crayfish and shrimp.... no favor... disappointed...
Great night at Fog Harbor Fish House. Our server was Daniel C.   He was awesome. The apple crisp was the best ever.

This is one of the best spots in the neighborhood. Everything I’ve tried is delicious but the soft shell crab sandwich and broccoli salad are my favorites. Even pre-pandemic Lolo’s was one of the few spots to have heated outdoor seating. Love it. Will be back!
Very clean and accessible place. They serve large meals and for inexpensive prices. I liked the food a lot and the waiters were super personal and chatty. I recommend this place.

The rum punch is amazing and the staff are extremely attentive and kind. I had the fish tacos which I was very excited to try. Unfortunately they had bones in them which I would prefer they hadn’t. There was nothing on the menu that had indicated there were bones present in the fish. I couldn’t finish the tacos but would definitely try this place again if they offer boneless fish tacos.
This place is soooooo good!!! I will definitely go back to eat there when I come to NY omg!thank youuu
Unhappy about price paid for amount of food. Small portion.  Small selection of menu items.
(Translated by Google) A little purple but good attention  (Original) Un poco de morados pero buena atención
I simply enjoy their dishes. I always get fantastic customer service there. The place is well organised and the cashiers are always kind. I highly recommend this place.
The person who took our order was very nasty  👀💩
I've visited several times and have always enjoyed the meal and service. My favorite dishes have to be the shellfish platter and risotto. I would definitely recommend this to family and friends

Love love love this place. Ive been going here for forever and the atmosphere is amazing and the food even better. I have been ordering weekly! The food is always hot and fresh when delivered.  The delivery is quick. And when you call you are always greeted with a friendly and competent person.
This is the best garlic shrimp boil I've ever had!!! People there are really nice. Manager helped pick out my dinner and I must say I am pleased with what he chose!!!
I love the fact Lolos is very prompt with their service. The food is very tasty!! Definitely a great place to visit especially when in Harlem!

Wanted to make this my first review 😋  I Was craving a seafood boil and coconut shrimp, this is one of the only restaurants to offer both ... And so much more! I ordered a variety of things because I couldn't decide 🙃  The snow crab legs with coconut curry is such a great way to take a break from the classic old bay and garlic butter sauce ( which is bomb too, my fiance had that flavor) The softshell crab sandwich was on point The coconut shrimp satisfied my craving and MORE especially with those yummy garlic fries  The customer service  topped off the whole experience. They were fast and helpful.  Definitely will return

LOVE Lolo's! Best Seafood in NYC, I enjoyed a flight of crab legs and delicious wings and hands down the best mix of quality products and generous service! The taste and flavors of the Islands on full culinary display at Lolo's!!

Love the freshness of the salmon, shrimp and snow crab legs. That's a big thing for me and they passed the test. Tip: get a bunch of things to share, me friends and I got to try a little bit if everything. The coconut curry sauce is amazing for any of the boils, it's creamy and dairy free. I love the plantain chips and and pineapple salsa dips. Overall quality and speed is amazing for food this fresh.

This place is amazing! I lived and worked on the UWS for years.  They are clean,  friendly, and have quality delicious food. Also a very unique menu. When you feel like having something but tired of the run of the mill take out. Call Lolo's!.

This is a one-of-a-kind gem in Harlem with an amazing heated back area to sit and relax, very friendly staff and fast service, I feel like I'm in another place besides New York! I'm here to tell you to order the JOHNNY CAKES. Are you kidding me? this is the best thing I think I've ever tasted and if I'm anywhere near LoLo's I always take a detour to get one.

Two stars does not reflect on the service but on the quality of the food. I came here with my boyfriend in the mood for some seafood boil. He ordered a shrimp steam pot and it was flavorless. It tasted like a bag of shrimps in butter. As for my order, I ordered coconut shrimps and lolo fries. The fries were good, the shrimps were dry and tasteless aswell and small quantity for the price we paid. Service was great but the food was terribly bland. Would not recommend.

Flavorless shrimp swimming in a pool of butter.  Need I say more? You know what I'm so disappointed I'll say a bit more. This restaurant doesn't belong in a place like Harlem PERIOD.. Go to light house .

First I Wanna Say How Small The Portion Of Salmon It Was .... They Cut A Salmon Steak in Half ... How U Serve Someone Half Of Something ??? Secondly The Salmon Was 🥴 I Order it To Be Flavored W Old Bay And Garlic , Why Is My Salmon Sweet 🤢🤢 I Didn’t Ask For A Glaze ! I Wanted Savory Salmon But Instead I Got Swedish Fish 😢😩😩😩 I’m So Displeased
Once upon a time this place had great food. Certain if not all items on the menu are frozen and not fresh. The staff changes every so often so the customer service is hit or miss.

Ordered my food online, and went to pick it up. They call you when your food is ready. The Crab cake sandwich is good. I ordered the Coconut Shrimp & Fries. You can taste the Coconut, but it is dry. The Nachos with Crab Dip is a waste. I didn't like the Crab Dip at all. Hopefully the other  food on the menu is better.

Super tasty Carribean themed restaurant where everything plate is perfectly cooked and spiced to perfection. There sandwiches are perfect for picnic in the park or lazy couches themed dinners. Definitely try the brunch options on the weekend as they are all super tasty and filling! Dont forget the LOLOS Punch either - will make you feel like your on the beach minus the concrete!!!

Bought a dinner for 2 from Pulse which came with came with  2 rum punches and a meal.  The lady in the window had a serious attitude problem as we tried to explain it was our first time there and didn't know the protocol. She just kept telling us to wait.. wait as we had a different menu then  that  which was on display. 30 minutes later when we got our food, which was very good but the rum punch was made with sorrel and had absolutely no rum  in it and for this I give 2 stars. When we went back to her to let her know our order had been mishandled. She declined  giving us new drinks stating that that's how they made theirs. yuck.
Food is all right portions are pretty small after I ate my meal I went to lighthouse just to get another meal.
A favorite spot for tasty seafood. i really loved this place.
Great space. They have curbside with heat lamps!
The seasonal pumpkin soup with crab and shrimp is very tasty!  Cute outdoor area for seating as well.
Skai and the Lolo’s team are excellent. Can’t wait to go back again — and you have to try the Sweet Plantains 😌
Ordered the shark bake and they gave catfish
Great food. Friendly and professional staff.
LoLo's reminds me of a Caribbean beachside restaurant. The food and drinks are delicious! Every dish is made to order. One of my go to place to eat in Harlem.

when i first went i wanted to support a local business but i guess local means inconsistent which is unfortunate that you tout to be black owned in a predominately black neighborhood... coconut shrimp tasted like breaded shrimp, no coconut , fries was cold and i was charged extra for some weird sauce and wasnt told nor is it marked on the menu anywhere as an option , wings was aiight until the sweetness became so overwhelming i though i was eating sugar... cook at home people

So my bf & I had our 1st date here late September. There was no wait to sit, which I loved. The drinks were strong=another plus. I ordered the crab cakes and was disappointed to find they were so small. They only come 2 in a order so I was still hungry. I had to order the shrimp and dirty rice. We also got the cauliflower as appetizer. The food tasted mediocre, nothing to do flips over. I would suggest more seasoning to the cooks. My bf got fish & he was satisfied. Overall, I wouldn't return.
Nice location for quality seafood. Loved this place from the first taste. The staff was very friendly and kind.
Food is good, would not get drinks here though. The mango drink had no alcohol in it all. Would rate higher but I feel like I wasted my money.
Good food great prices

Tasty lobster roll, very generous with the meat, served up on a Johnny cake with sliced avocado. Pretty great. Lolo's fries were a real nice side, as was the durty rice and corn. Called in my order and it was ready pretty quickly. Cool little spot, nice people. Thanks for taking care of me and feeding my lobster craving!
Excellent

Was ok. Ordered the shrimp and crab. Shrimps were way too big and over cooked. Everything came in a bag and was super messy, the butter they used wasnt butter but flavored oil... Id go back if they made a few changes. Serve real butter on the side, use medium shrimp in your buckets, and employ more napkins

OMG! I really enjoyed the shrimp & fish tacos. But the coconut shrimp springs rolls could easily become a new addiction for me. I really enjoyed the savory blends of spices. I had take out and all of the food was delicious.
Good good and service, a great place to get seafood. Definitely recommend
It felt like a secret. Tiny window and delicious food!!
One of my fav places for quality seafood. Entered near eleven, it wasn't packed. The service here is attentive. The place has a nice atmosphere.

Great crab legs, enjoyed the garlic butter sauce.  The pom pom shrimp were good.  I'm a pass on the conch fritters but my offspring enjoyed them.  I'm also a hard pass on the rum punch, but then again, I'm a straight whiskey sipper so....  The mango drink (we had virgins) were delicious.  I would definitely go again.
Island Time!! Change ur Latitude.. change ur Attitude!!!

The seafood tastes delicious but they could be more generous with the seasonings. I thought the rum punch had no alcohol which was a disappointment. We used pulsd which the restaurant was completely unaware of until I showed it to them. I doubt I'll return but I'd recommend
The BEST Soft shell crab and bake EVER!!
😢 sorry to say cod chip so hard it was like chewing an eraser.

Great stop at reasonable prices. This is essentially a food truck with covered tables. Fish and shrimp were excellent. Some of the best I ever had and that includes the UK. Wait might be long because everything is made fresh.

I got the fish n chips and also a order of their fish tacos along with a side of crazy garlic fries... the fish had a real thin but clean crispy texture.. it was prepared really well but I'm not much of a fish n chips kinda guy .. it was kinda bland for my taste buds but the preparation was really well!

I was actually waiting on Harlem Tavern to be seated and I seen this little spot around the corner. My bf and I looked at the menu and seen it looked way better then Harlem Tavern so we came here instead. I had the garlic fries and fried fish and it was to die for. The garlic fries was sooo tasty. My bf had the shrimp with salmon and duty rice with broccoli and it was amazing. I also had crab dip. Everything tasted so good and fresh. It’s really a hole in the wall. I will be back soon !! I wish I could rate this place a 10 star.

The food is great don’t get me wrong. But it’s a trip from where we live to get over here. We got the food all the way home to see that they gave us salmon which I will NOT eat. So we call to make sure the correct order is ready when we get there. We get there more than 30 minutes later and it’s not ready. Then they had the nerve to act like they did us a favor to let us keep food that I won’t eat!! I have to really reconsider whether I’ll be back. The food is good but if it’s going to be a hassle every time it’s really not worth it.  Edit/update: we’re finally home to eat and the food is just okay this time. Very disappointed.

I like this restaurant! They serve excellent dishes, their menu is varied, The chef in that restaurant is a specialist, I love a lot trying all their food. The dishes are consistently fresh and tasty, the attitude towards the clients  is nice. I frequently visit this restaurant and I was never discontended. I recommend it with no hesitation.
Good
Legit British fish and chips. No doubt about it, this will be a for sure part of your restaurant rotation. So what if it's near a tourist trap? The food would sell in the UK as one of their best.
Good location
Great food, good serving, chased it down with a frozen mango slush which comes with or without alcohol..delicious
(Translated by Google) My work's place  (Original) Mi lugar de trabajo
Everything was perfect, they got something special goin on there.
Great spot for a quick tasty bite.
Excellent!

Although we have frequented Moonshadows for over 40 years, I believe last week was the first time in 20 years we had lunch in the dining room.  It was fabulous!!  We had family in town and wanted to escape the heat of the Valley and Moonshadows seemed a great respite.  All four of us were pleasantly surprised how wonderful the food and the service was excellent.  I'm still reeling about the chicken sandwich on ciabatta bread with pesto sauce and whatever else yummy ingredients made their way to this excellent, decadent, amazing sandwich.  I have been begging my husband to take me to Moonshadows just to have the chicken sandwich.  The rest of us had a burger which was devoured by my 84 year old Father-in-law, both girls had the coveted beet salad with grilled chicken which they loved.
I Am Extremely  Interested  In The Place, But Had To At A Comment,  Just To Get Your Reviews Off 666!!! Lol

Such rude service here hot day had ask 3 times to open the umbrellas! Then ordered fried shrimp but instead received steam. Spoke to lady at the window she said she repeated the order with attitude. Yeah so much for local eats.

I ordered the Crab Legs and Shrimp Steampot and a side of garlic noodles and the food was not seasoned enough, had no real flavor and the noodles were dry. It was not a good impression for a first time visit. I will try one more time since I'm trying to support black owned businesses.

Ordered to go and didn’t have to wait for very long at all surprisingly. Ordered the steam pot combo with 1lb Snow Crabs and 1/2 lb of Shrimp. Both delicious. I’d recommend the Garlic butter with Old Bay Seasoning. Also got a mango margarita to-go in a portable plastic container. Great food and great service. Will def come back!

There signature sauce wasn’t good at all, it tasted like a watered down milky curry sauce with a sweet taste to it. They need to experiment more on a better sauce! Crab legs where good the salmon didn’t taste the best. There dirty rice had the same signature sauce so I couldn’t finish the rice.

So i ordered food from here, decided to try it.  Guac was freshly made. ✔  The "rum punch" which was sorrel was refreshing not much of a rum punch.  Now the seafood boiled peeled shrimp, maybe that means something to others because i expected PEELED CLEANED/ DEVEINED shrimps. And the person taking order asked repeated (peeled, peeled?) Yes peeled. Got the food, aNd NOT PEELED!  Now i literally had to peel this. clean it and recook it. I only did it because the meals were bloody pricey. This with the salmon and shrimp and rice.  This meal however, turned me completely off.
Very hidden gem. Recomended 100 %.

I normally love this restaurant and order from here often, but something has been up as of late. I ordered takeout earlier and after waiting an hour past the estimated delivery time it finally arrived, cold and unappetizing. Total waste of money. Recent reviews on Seamless mirror my same comments. I wish I had read them first:( Really hope they will pick back up their level of service.
That butter sauce I tell you omg..all the from Jersey City...big up... keep making me happy..like jamaica.😝
Flavorful and fresh.   Always worth the trip
I like to think this is our secret spot for Caribbean fare, then again - what do we know! We come back time & time again, thank you!
The food was delicious especially the seafood boil with coco curry.  Ordered take out and ate in the car I could not wait!  This restaurant is definitely a must try 😋
Just had the shark and bake and it was delicious! Fast and friendly service, just a man nbc nvm n v co nbc v cbc great experience all around.
Had my first visit to LoLo's today and it was amazing! My order came out super quick and the salmon warm bowl was even better than i expected it to be. Definitely going to stop by again!

I’ve been going to Lolo’s since it opened and it is hands down the best seafood I’ve eaten in years. Their colorful decor matches the spectrums of flavors and taste that I’ve experienced at Lolo’s. I recommend the Salmon / Shrimp combo as well as the Johnny cakes!
My throat HURTS from the amount of salt they put in this awful food (salmon bowl) - salmon tasted old and unseasoned, rice is DRENCHED in salt. Worst meal I’ve ever had in NYC.
Seafood smells like ammonia. They tried their best to make up for it with free meals to go but I will still charged for my initial meal that was clearly spoiled.
Very good def try it once

I placed an order with Uber eats , crab legs , Shrimps , Corn on the Cobb . Me and my daughter noticed  black spots on the crab legs , the shrimps wasn’t cooked . I google black spots on crab legs and a picture of a crab leg popped up with black spots and they were Leeches i wouldn’t recommend they do not care for the community , especially around this testing time I have pictures if I can load them on here I will  ....

Ordered by phone at 5:23 and walked away with the food at 6:16 after being told “20” mins at 5:23. Seems like seamless or Uber eats is the way to go as I saw a steady stream of delivery people walking in and out with food. Attempting to give this business more money without them having to pay fees to seamless worked to my detriment. Food smells good.

I went to Lolos for a Mothers Day dinner.  I was very disappointed because bite sized appetizer type snack meals.  For $66.00 I think this restaurant is very overrated.  I have never eaten from the South to East coast seafood boil with sweet potatoes.  The fish  and chicken  was old  and dry and prepared/fried in oil that was not fresh.   This was not a way I wanted my Mother’s Day to end especially since I traveled from up state!
Ordered two servings on delivery app, got only one of them.

Lolo's is so freaking good.  I've been going here for years but wanted to say that I've ordered take-out since the CoVid shutdown began (call in your order and help them avoid the Seamless fees!) and the food was just as good, on time, service was great.  Miss these guys and hope I'll be able to have some garlic fries and a beer in the backyard soon.
Fav place ever ! Very cozy
NICE SPOT IN HARLEM HIDDEN TREASURE......
I smashed the food and the waitress later that night ;)

As soon as we walked in the young lady at the counter greeted us gave us sometime to look over the menu and answered all of our questions without attitude. She was very thorough with all of her answers regarding the food we were asking about. It's a pretty small space, you definitely could not do a large party in there. But, what they lack in space they make up for in pleasantness, professionalism, politeness and definitely good food! My new "food to go spot" for sure. I love supporting a business like this!
Interesting, scenery unexpected

Loved it! The food was excellent and the service was amazing. I will definitely come back when I'm in NYC again. I ordered the crab cake basket and the crabby dip with plantains and it was delicious. If you're thinking about stopping by, don't hesitate!
Great food.... 4th time going there
Service suck! Food nasty

Overall, I like the food because its freshly prepared. This was my 3rd time getting takeout from Lolo's. The food is not consistent. I ordered the fish basket all three times. Twice it was overcooked and dry plus they forgot an item. Although, they were tasty, the plaintain chips and salsa is overpriced for the quantity that you get.
Would like stronger seasoning but other wise amazing great prices

The food is overpriced. We went on a cold Saturday night hoping to eat in warmth however the eating area was extremely cold because it is not insulated properly. We spent over 80 dollars and the sliver ware was plastic and the plates were throw away tin pans. The staff were friendly trying to over compensate for the environment which is extremely low level for the price being paid. Another downer is you have to pay before ordering; this is disappointing because if you actually saw the eating area you would move on to a more desirable eating destination. Bottom line, this establishment needs to modulate their pricing and upgrade their environment before I would spend another dollar!
I regularly arrive getting some food in this place. I loved the quick service and well made food. Highly recommended.
We had the jerk ribs and snow crab legs in the Lolo’s special sauce. They were fabulous! We are excited to come back soon! The service was really wonderful as well.

Very well kept and accessible spot. They serve big portions and for inexpensive rates. I enjoyed the menu very much and the waiters were very amiable and informative. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.
Good food like in the caribian but the puch are not so good .
Love it clean kitchen shack style..awsome food creation.
You guys made my birthday really special

Good experience. Great food and excellent service. The people who work here are really good at making the service great. I like the vibe with the whole decor and environ at Lolo's. It's a good place to have a chat with friends and have an amazing meal.

We enjoy eating out. Yesterday we came to this superb place which friends recommended to us. We enjoyed a beautiful evening there with excellent meal and  an experienced crew and a talented cook. We  added this venue in our phone list  and we shall no doubt return soon.  Highly recommended.
Best seafood I've had in a while! Good price and portions
Food is not that bad not to expensive

I hadn't had seafood in a while and was referred to try Lolo's from a friend, and this place did not disappoint! I ate the crab cake with durty rice and it was absolutely delicious, especially for being under $20!
Oooof love this spot. Coconut curry sauce all up in there. Yes please. @swethadoesyoga
Yes, the food was great
Great seafood and love the atmosphere!
Conch fritters & garlic fries. Banging. The rice is so flavorful. Can't go wrong here
Staff is super welcoming and helpful when it comes to suggestions. Me and my girlfriends went and had a lovely time. The food is absolutely delicious and cooked to order!!
Unique little caribbean seafood spot
Great place! Good food.
Good for the soul meals. A bit high priced & have to wait a bit but, it is worth it.

Took so long for two small orders to be made and they weren't worth the wait time at all. Wasn't so bad but definitely not the best seafood spot. I had shrimp and fries, my coworker and some sort of fish sand which with fries.
Shhhhh!  These are the best ribs in Harlem. Don't tell anyone please.  Wonderful seafood, great bake and shark. The staff is always friendly and professional.  Be sure to catch their happy hour.
Prefer food/drinks not on paper/plastic.
Delicious
I love this little Mom and Pop's seafood restaurant in Harlem, lobster so fresh with different choices of favors.

Really cute place, it looks small but there's several seating in the back and the seating theme is like Caribbean shacks but they have heat so it wasn't bad when we went in November. The food was really good and reasonably priced, the restaurant even gave my friend a bday cake on the house!
Great happy hour!!

Really good seafood 🦞.  I had the coconut 🥥 shrimp 🍤.  I also sat in the back and enjoyed a glass of wine 🍷.  The prices are a bit pricey for what you get,  but overall it was a good experience.  Customer service level was very good.  And I went on a Sunday afternoon and it was not crowded.
Great little place
Great local spot for crab legs

The sauces are good but I'm skeptical of serving streaming food in plastic bags. Too much disposable ware. The fries are good, but over all I think this place shouldn't be on the 1000 best of NYC. Go once, that's enough. Vietnamese Cajun does crawfish better. The crab shack aesthetic is cool. Good service. Pretty fast. Decent prices.
It's a little whole in the wall.. Food was average but over priced.  I left there with eo many mosquito bites. Just not a good experience
Shark and bake were outstanding! The garlic fries were very oily and the garlic sauce wasnt that garlicky. Maybe I'm too used to Mojo sauce.

This place food gets progressively worst, and I try to give them the benefit of the doubt anytime I order, but I will never eat here again.... Even for free. I had pom pom shrimp today and I couldn't eat one. It literally tasted unclean and unseasoned, Ughhh just disgusting. Food is either, undercooked or not edible.. Too bad the owner seem to be a professional but as for the chef a replacement NEED to be in order
A date a one of my favorite places with my favorite guy! Labor Day turn up
Wasn't bad better than expected. Only complaint was seating but I get the concept behind the shack.

So a Friend put me on, I live in the Area and always looking for a Dope spot to bring a Date. Was in the Area and decided to give it a try. Order some food to take out. Great ambiance,  one of the Servers noticed I was waiting for my food and gave me complimentary chips and Dip. It was Amazing and the Coconut Shrimp and Fritters was Immaculate.
The best coconut shrimp Ive ever had!
The food was good, but use dairy in most and I can't consume dairy.
Great seafood restaurant with a big outdoor seating area. Always busy, especially weekends.
Tastes amazing
Basic menu, basic food, basically
Good food, reasonably priced. Hits the spot well if you stay in Harlem and are craving spicy seafood!

The most horrible experience I ever had. I mean the service is extremely slow I mean extremely extremely slow and the attitude of the staff were let me say it weigh less than professional not to add that the place was a mess
Food is excellent and the price is great. A must if you love seafood.
The outdoor lounge is the back is truly and escape, even in the rain... Black folks have created a beautiful environment. And the conch fritters are amazing.
The best meal I have ever had. So delicious!
Unconventional but delicious. Had so much fun. Definitely going back!
Always treated fair when I’m in attendance. Crab legs seem a little small but definitely a fan of the cuisine.
Best avocado toast!
Jerk chicked was salty. The bread was delicious. Not enough conch in the conch fritters. Cauliflower was good.
Wow, seriously so good. Shark sandwich was bomb. Fruit punch was bomb. Outdoor seating was pleasant. Service was super nice.
This place never fails to impress. They have excellent dishes for convenient pricing, there no long wait even when the spot is full.

Food at LoLo's is excellent. The crab cakes are a must! The space is small but they use every inch for seating customers and cooking. They bring the real feeling of island eatery huts. Staff is great!
Great island feel out back in patio area
Crab legs were great, and I loved down to earth environment.
Great spot to pick up exotic cuisine
The fried Whiting,  shrimp or fritters did not have any flavor. But the garlic French fries were tasty.

The Shark + Bake sandwich is the best fish sandwich I’ve ever had. Better than any crab cake sandwich I had during college in Annapolis, MD, and better than any Grouper sandwich I’ve had while visiting my mother in law in Naples, Florida. It’s salty, sweet, and sublime.  It’s a showstopper.

Lolos is a really tasty seafood joint with Caribbean flare. I had the crab cake sandwich, rum punch, and plantains. Sandwich was pretty good although a side is not included. Rum punch was yummy but not very strong. Plantains were everything. Nice sweet and savory combo with cheese and toppings.  Keep in mind that it is smaller with limited seating. Conversations can certainly be heard across the room. They do have a heated cabana but I didn't check it out.
